r575 | foobum | 2011-11-23 01:15:33 +0000 (Wed, 23 Nov 2011) | 2 lines

Due to a bug in Honeycomb it was possible to cause a crash on startup if you configured a backend address containing a space. This was obviously difficult for a user to recover from!
Fix by verifying that the backend address doesn't contain spaces when the preference is changed, being more permissive wrt leading or trailing whitespace and by avoiding the bug in case we've already stored a value with a space using a version that is younger than this commit
